# Content Voice

Read SOUL.md for full philosophy. Apply these when writing or editing concept pages.

## Three-Moment Rule

Every concept page must create:

1. **"Oh, I've seen this before"** — analogy lands in `#hook` and `#interactive-viz`
2. **"Now I get why this is hard"** — failure visible in `#why-it-matters`
3. **"I could explain this to someone else"** — quiz passed in `#check-understanding`

## Voice

- Direct and concrete, not academic
- Use "you" and "your corpus" — address practitioners
- Short sentences, active verbs
- Take positions — no hedging
- Concrete examples over abstract principles

## Banned patterns

- Definition before analogy
- Passive consumption (no "read this paragraph" without interaction)
- Multiple concepts per page
- Quiz as optional bonus — quiz is the gate

## Progressive disclosure

TL;DR → Visual → Details → Tradeoffs → Quiz. A reader should grasp the core idea from the first three sections without reading technical details.
